#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:36
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&basket; still does not have a handbook, so contributors are welcome! Check "
"the <ulink url=\"https://l10n.kde.org/docs/doc-primer/index.html\"> KDE "
"documentation</ulink> for the hints on the DocBook format."
msgstr ""
"&basket; 尚无使用手册，欢迎贡献者参与编写！有关 DocBook 格式的提示，请查看 "
"<ulink url=\"https://l10n.kde.org/docs/doc-primer/index.html\"> KDE 文档</"
"ulink> 。 "

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:39
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Meanwhile, you can look for help on the Internet. In particular, look "
"through the <ulink url=\"https://basket-notepads.github.io\">old website</"
"ulink> or check Linux magazines if you have access to them, for example:"
msgstr ""
"与此同时，你可以在互联网上寻求帮助。尤其可以浏览 <ulink url=\"https://basket-"
"notepads.github.io\">旧网站</ulink> ，或者如果你能获取 Linux 相关杂志的话，也"
"可以查阅，例如："

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:43
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<quote>Tutorial: Basket: Capture your thoughts.</quote> Linux Format 120 "
"(Andy Channelle)"
msgstr ""
"<quote>教程： Basket ：记录你的想法</quote> Linux Format 第120 期 (作者："
"Andy Channelle) "

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:47
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<quote>A Virtual Basket. Storing, sorting, and filing with KDE&apos;s "
"Basket</quote> Linux Magazine 54 (Stefanie Teufel)"
msgstr ""
"<quote>一个虚拟笔记栏：借助 KDE 的 Basket 进行存储、分类与归档</quote> Linux "
"Magazine 第54期 (作者：Stefanie Teufel) "

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:56 index.docbook:103
#, no-c-format
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr "简介"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:57
#, no-c-format
msgid "&basket; is mainly an all-purpose notes taker, but a particular one:"
msgstr "&basket;主要是一款通用的笔记记录工具，但它别具特色："

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:61
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using BasKet"
msgstr "使用 BasKet 笔记篮"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:64
#, no-c-format
msgid "Version Sync"
msgstr "版本同步"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:65
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When enabled, Version Sync puts your baskets and notes under version "
"control. Currently this is an experimental feature and only very basic "
"functions are implemented, so it may require additional software and some "
"manual setup. These are some of the things that can be done using external "
"tools (but not Basket interface yet):"
msgstr ""
"启用后，版本同步功能会将您的笔记篮和笔记置于版本控制之下。目前这是一项实验性"
"特性，仅实现了非常基础的功能，因此可能需要额外的软件以及一些手动设置。以下是"
"一些可以借助外部工具完成的事情 (但目前还无法通过 Basket 界面实现) ："

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:68
#, no-c-format
msgid "check out old revisions and revert the changes"
msgstr "查看旧版本并恢复更改"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:71
#, no-c-format
msgid "synchronize baskets on several computers (merge the changes)"
msgstr "在几台计算机上同步笔记篮 (合并更改) "

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:74
#, no-c-format
msgid "push baskets backup to remote repository"
msgstr "推送笔记篮备份到远程仓库"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:77
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To enable it, select <menuchoice> <guimenu>Settings</guimenu> "
"<guimenuitem>Configure BasKet Note Pads</guimenuitem> </menuchoice> → "
"<guibutton>Version Sync</guibutton> and <guibutton>Enable distributed "
"version control</guibutton>. It will initialize git repository in "
"<filename>~/.kde/share/apps/basket/baskets</filename>, upon which standard "
"git tools can be used."
msgstr ""
"要启用该功能，依次选择<menuchoice> <guimenu>设置</guimenu> <guimenuitem>配置 "
"BasKet 记事贴本</guimenuitem> </menuchoice> → <guibutton>版本同步</"
"guibutton> 以及 <guibutton>启用分布式版本控制</guibutton> 。这会在"
"<filename>~/.kde/share/apps/basket/baskets</filename> 中初始化一个 Git 仓库，"
"之后就可以使用标准的 Git 工具了。"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:84
#, no-c-format
msgid "Clearing version history"
msgstr "清除版本历史记录"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:85
#, no-c-format
msgid "Clearing the history can be useful in these cases:"
msgstr "在这些情况下，清理历史可能是有用的："

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:88
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"you have locked a basket and want to remove any previous unencrypted "
"versions (which are still stored in the system)"
msgstr ""
"您已锁定一个笔记篮，并且想要删除之前任何未加密的版本 (这些版本仍存储在系统"
"中) "

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:91
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"you want to free some disk space (can be topical if you insert a lot of "
"images or other files into Basket)"
msgstr ""
"您想要释放一些磁盘空间 (如果你在 Basket 中插入了大量图片或其他文件，这就很有"
"必要) "

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:94
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Note that you will have to redo any manual setup you did on the git "
"repository."
msgstr "请注意，你将不得不重新进行之前在 Git 仓库上所做的任何手动设置。"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:100
#, no-c-format
msgid "BasKet file structure"
msgstr "BasKet 文件结构"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:108
#, no-c-format
msgid "BasKet Archive file format"
msgstr "BasKet 存档文件格式"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:109
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The BasKet file format (.baskets) is a structure which wraps a compressed "
"tar and a preview image. The latest archive format version is 0.6.1."
msgstr ""
"BasKet 文件格式 (.baskets）是一种包含压缩的tar文件和一张预览图像的结构。最新"
"的存档格式版本是0.6.1。"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:112
#, no-c-format
msgid "File Structure"
msgstr "文件结构"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:113
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The archive file is divided into the structures: file header, preview image "
"header, a preview image (.png), archive header, and a gunzipped tar archive "
"(.tar.gz) containing a baskets file tree as illustrated in the following "
"sketch"
msgstr ""
"该存档文件分为以下结构：文件头、预览图像头、预览图像 ( .png 格式）、存档头，"
"以及一个经过 gzip 解压的 tar 存档 ( .tar.gz 格式) ，其中包含一个 baskets 文件"
"树，如下图所示。 "

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:121
#, no-c-format
msgid "Archive file header"
msgstr "存档文件头"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:122
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The file header is a short structure, consisting of lines of strings, the "
"file declarator, and the format version"
msgstr "文件头是一个简短的结构，由字符串行、文件声明符和格式版本组成。"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:124
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The first 17 bytes contain the literal string <code>BasKetNP:archive</code> "
"followed by a new line feed symbol (0x0A) in ISO-8859-1 encoding."
msgstr ""
"前17个字节包含文本字符串<code>BasKetNP:archive</code>，其后紧跟一个采用"
"ISO-8859-1编码的换行符 (0x0A) 。"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:125
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The second string is a literal string <code>version:0.6.1</code> followed by "
"a line feed symbol (0x0A) in ISO-8859-1 encoding."
msgstr ""
"第二个字符串是文本字符串 <code>version:0.6.1</code>，后面跟着一个采用"
"ISO-8859-1编码的换行符 (0x0A) 。"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:126 index.docbook:134 index.docbook:147
#, no-c-format
msgid "An example:"
msgstr "举个例子："

#. Tag: programlisting
#: index.docbook:127
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<![CDATA[\n"
"BasKetNP:archive\n"
"version:0.6.1\n"
"                                                                        ]]>"
msgstr ""
"<![CDATA[\n"
"BasKetNP:archive\n"
"version:0.6.1\n"
"                                                                        ]]>"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:131
#, no-c-format
msgid "Preview image header"
msgstr "预览图像头"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:132
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Currently, the basket archive file contains a preview file which is derived "
"from the first basket's content."
msgstr ""
"目前，Basket 存档文件包含一个预览文件，该预览文件由第一个笔记篮的内容生成。 "

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:133
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Directly following the file header, a literal string "
"<code>preview*:&lt;size&gt;</code> in ISO-8859-1 encoding, again followed by "
"a line feed symbol. The parameter <code>&lt;size&gt;</code> is a string of "
"decimal numbers. It declares the size in bytes of the preview image. "
"<code>&lt;size&gt;</code> is of type unsigned long."
msgstr ""
"紧接在文件头之后的是一个采用 ISO-8859-1 编码的文本字符串 "
"<code>preview*:&lt;size&gt;</code>，同样后面跟有一个换行符。参数 "
"<code>&lt;size&gt;</code> 是一串十进制数字。它声明了预览图像的字节大小。"
"<code>&lt;size&gt;</code> 的类型是无符号长整型。"

#. Tag: programlisting
#: index.docbook:135
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<![CDATA[\n"
"preview*:12000\n"
"                                                                        ]]>"
msgstr ""
"<![CDATA[\n"
"preview*:12000\n"
"                                                                        ]]>"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:139
#, no-c-format
msgid "Preview image file"
msgstr "预览图像文件"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:140
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The preview image is of type .png. Its size is specified by the preview "
"image header. The preview image file is inserted as file stream, and "
"directly follows the preview image header."
msgstr ""
"预览图像格式为 .png 。其大小由预览图像头部指定。预览图像文件以文件流形式插"
"入，紧跟在预览图像头之后。 "

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:144
#, no-c-format
msgid "BasKet content archive header"
msgstr "BasKet 内容归档头"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:145
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Just like for the preview image file, the content archive is preceded by a "
"string specifying its size. That string directly follows the file stream of "
"the archive."
msgstr ""
"与预览图像文件类似，内容存档文件之前有一个字符串，用于指定其大小。该字符串紧"
"跟在存档的文件流之后。 "

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:146
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"That string must be <code>archive*:&lt;size&gt;</code> followed by a line "
"feed symbol, in ISO-8869-1 encoding. The parameter <code>&lt;size&gt;</code> "
"is a unsigned long integer in string format."
msgstr ""
"该字符串必须按照 ISO-8869-1 标准编码，格式为<code>archive*:&lt;size&gt;</"
"code> ，后面跟一个换行符。参数<code>&lt;size&gt;</code> 是以字符串格式表示的"
"无符号长整型整数。"

#. Tag: programlisting
#: index.docbook:148
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<![CDATA[\n"
"archive*:1245000\n"
"                                                                        ]]>"
msgstr ""
"<![CDATA[\n"
"archive*:1245000\n"
"                                                                        ]]>"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:152
#, no-c-format
msgid "BasKet content archive"
msgstr "BasKet 内容存档"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:153
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The content archive contains the BasKet file tree compressed in to a gzipped "
"tar archive (.tar.gz). Its size is specified by the content header."
msgstr ""
"内容存档包含压缩为gzip格式的tar归档文件（.tar.gz）的BasKet文件树。其大小由内"
"容标头指定。 "

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:157
#, no-c-format
msgid "Example byte stream"
msgstr "示例字节流"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:158
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The following table shows key parts of the basket archive file content. The "
"left column specifies the offset in the file stream. The center column gives "
"the byte stream at the current offset in hexadecimal format. The right "
"column shows printable characters within the file stream at the current "
"offset."
msgstr ""
"下表展示了 BasKet 归档文件内容的关键部分。左列指定了文件流中的偏移量。中间列"
"以十六进制格式给出了当前偏移量处的字节流。右列显示了当前偏移量处文件流中的可"
"打印字符。"

